value.title: Biden's road trip starts as partisan paths loom larger: The Note
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris hit the road -- a series of trips to mark 100 days in office that could define what the next 1,000 or so look like.

value.title: Biden's 100 days in office: Is America back open? COVID outbreak check, status of schools, mask guidelines
value.excerpt: President Biden is now 100 days into his term in office, a marker that leaders often point to when promising to hit the ground running and get things done for the American people. Here is what he has accomplished -- and what remains the same -- when it comes to the coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: AOC Praises Activists, Says 'Keep Going' After Joe Biden Speech
value.excerpt: The Democratic congresswoman Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez praised progressive activists on Wednesday night after President Joe Biden put forth his record and future plans in a speech to a joint session of Congress.

value.title: 'Woke cancel culture movement' backfired on Joe Biden, Stacey Abrams: Gov. Kemp
value.excerpt: Georgia Gov. Brian Kemp told “Fox & Friends” Thursday, President Biden and Georgia voting rights activist Stacey Abrams has driven the “far-reaching, woke cancel culture movement” too far and now it has backfired on the Democratic Party for “lying” about the state’s election law.

value.title: Kamala Harris agrees with Tim Scott that the US is not racist, but says racism must not be ignored
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris on Thursday agreed with South Carolina Sen. Tim Scott that the United States is not a racist country, but added that the nation has a history of racism that cannot be overlooked.

value.title: Kamala Harris to visit Milwaukee on Tuesday: reports
value.excerpt: The vice president on Tuesday will travel to Milwaukee, according to reports.

value.title: Harris lands new job pushing American Jobs Plan through Congress for Biden
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris was given a new assignment during President Biden’s address to Congress Wednesday night, tasked to lead the effort to push through his approximately $2 trillion American Jobs Plan.

value.title: How do Americans feel about President Trump?
value.excerpt: CBS News, along with YouGov, has tracked Americans' views on President Trump and his administration since he was sworn into office. CBS News elections director Anthony Salvanto joins CBSN with details on the latest poll.

value.title: Cheney: 'Wishful thinking' by Trump she won't seek 4th term
value.excerpt: Liz Cheney calls speculation by former President Donald Trump that she won’t seek re-election next year “wishful thinking.”

value.title: Donald Trump Suggests He May Sue CNN Over Project Veritas Video Allegedly Proving Bias
value.excerpt: "This is like a campaign contribution of magnitudes like nobody's ever seen before," former President Donald Trump said of a Project Veritas video that secretly recorded a CNN employee describing the network's reporting as anti-Trump "propaganda.

value.title: Catholic bishops could consider whether Biden should receive Communion
value.excerpt: The U.S. Conference of Catholic Bishops is holding a meeting in June to consider whether its Committee on Doctrine should draft a document clarifying the church's stance on abortion.

value.title: Trump adviser Roger Stone says he was in a "suspicious" hit and run car accident
value.excerpt: Roger Stone, long-time adviser and confidant of President Trump, claims he was the victim of a "suspicious" hit-and-run car accident Wednesday. The crash comes days after Stone admitted to CBS News that he had made contact with a suspected Russian hacker.

value.title: The Latest: Biden to say US 'turning peril into possibility'
value.excerpt: In his first address to Congress, President Joe Biden will declare that the nation is “turning peril into possibility, crisis into opportunity.”

value.title: Biden to keep intelligence inspector general Trump appointed
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden intends to keep the inspector general overseeing the U.S. intelligence community who was appointed by former President Donald Trump

value.title: Trump claims he would be on Mount Rushmore if he were a Democrat
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump on Wednesday claimed that his face would be added to Mount Rushmore if he were a Democrat. Trump’s allies have long flattered him with the idea that his

value.title: Biden's pick to serve on powerful DC-based appellate says her experience as a Black jurist 'might be valuable' if confirmed
value.excerpt: Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson, President Joe Biden's pick to fill a vacancy on a powerful DC-based appellate court, said at a Senate hearing Wednesday that her race doesn't play a role in her work as a judge, but that her experience as an African American jurist "might be valuable" should she be confirmed

value.title: President Biden nominates Texas Sheriff Ed Gonzalez to head ICE
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden has announced Sheriff Ed Gonzalez of Harris County, Texas, as his nominee for director of Immigration and Customs Enforcement. He was included on a list of 11 nominations for key national security positions.

value.title: Biden Energy Dept. nominee praises Green New Deal, calls for industry 'transformation' in new book
value.excerpt: President Biden's pick for an Energy Department leadership position has a new book in which she supports the Green New Deal and calls for a "power revolution" that would transform how the energy industry functions for the sake of combating socioeconomic inequality.

value.title: Kamala Harris' influencer niece, Meena, 'should create a firewall' between business and family, some ethics experts advise
value.excerpt: Meena Harris, the 36-year-old influencer niece of Vice President Kamala Harris, has raised concerns among some ethics experts due to her relationship with the VP.

value.title: Trump administration accuses Obama of wiretapping
value.excerpt: President Trump is calling for Congress to investigate his claim that the Obama administration wiretapped phones in Trump Tower during the presidential campaign. Associated Press White House reporter Vivian Salama joins CBSN to discuss.

value.title: How the Biden presidency looks from one pivotal Pennsylvania county, 100 days in
value.excerpt: Carol Erker vividly remembers the emotion that washed over her after Joe Biden won the 2020 election. Even as she worried about the pandemic and the Oval Office that Biden was inheriting, she felt like she could finally breathe.

value.title: 'Not an easy transition': Inside Trump's unconventional first months out of office
value.excerpt: Most Mondays and Tuesdays, former President Donald Trump skips golf to confer with aides about the week ahead.

value.title: D.C. officer who suffered heart attack on Jan. 6 calls out Trump for downplaying ‘brutal, savage’ riot

value.title: Tim Scott: What to know about Republican senator giving rebuttal to Biden address
value.excerpt: Sen. Tim Scott is the junior senator from South Carolina and a rising star in the GOP.

value.title: What Laura Italiano Said About the New York Post's Kamala Harris Book Story
value.excerpt: The journalist who wrote an article claiming that Vice President Kamala Harris' book was being distributed to migrant children has resigned from the New York Post,and said she was "ordered" to write the story.
